The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 Decibel distress

 A STAFF REPORTER

 The pollution control board (PCB) control room received frantic telephone calls from all over the city throughout Thursday evening, urging immediate action against crackers being burst in their areas.

 At least 25 complaints were registered with the PCB?s control room in the evening. Many complainants said there were old and ailing people at home.

Complaints poured in from Kasba, Baguiati, Lake Town, 

Dover Road, Cossipore, Loudon Street and near Baisakhi Abasan in Salt Lake. ?Most 

complaints are from Kasba, Lake Town and Baguiati,? said Sudip Banerjee, PCB chief.




